                        <provenance type="found" when="1854">Discovered c.1854 by Mr. R. Chearnley on a low wall beside a grave in the graveyard at Ardmore (Macalister 1945, 260). One of three ogham stones discovered at this site (see also I-WAT-002 and I-WAT-003). Other early features at Ardmore include St Declan's oratory, cathedral ruins (Romanesque), a round tower and a graveyard, all within a D-shaped enclosure (dims. c. 200m N-S; c. 130m E-W; WA040-008023-).
                        </provenance>
