            <div type="apparatus"/>
               
            
            <div type="translation"/>
               
            
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>This appears to be an example of a Latin name, <foreign xml:lang="la">Amatus</foreign> 'beloved', in an Irish ogham inscription (McManus 1991, 113). AMADU is also a possible example of an o-stem dative singular used here instead of the usual genitive.</p>
            </div>
